					<head>Perush Bava ḳama</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>The commentary of Abraham ben David of Posquières on Bava ḳama.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="tmr-Hebr">Hebrew, Aramaic</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="150v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Bava ḳama </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פירוש קמא </title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/8687273">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/8687273" xml:lang="en">Abraham ben David, of Posquières, approximately 1125-1198 </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/8687273" xml:lang="he">אברהם בן דוד, מפוסקיר, ראב"ד ה3, 1120-1198 </persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; Oriental (Syrian) semi-cursive script of the 13th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex.</support>
								<extent>150 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>258</height>
										<width>165</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>190</height>
										<width>115</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>150 folios (+ 1 modern paper flyleaf at the beginning and 3 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>i9: folios 1-9 (incomplete, the first leaf cancelled); ii10: folios 10-19, iii9: folios 20-28 (one leaf lost); iv-xiv10: folios 29-138; xv14-2: folios 139-150 (last two leaves lost).</p>
									<p>Catchwords at the end of the quires as well as the enumeration in Hebrew letters at the beginning nearly entirely preserved.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Imperfect at the beginning and at end. </p>
									<p>Some leaves damaged.</p>
									<p>Stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="24" writtenLines="24">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Chapter titles and initial words of sections written in larger characters.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Oriental (Syrian) semi-cursive script of the 13th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 1rhas a title written twice in two later hands. </p>
							<p>Folio 1rcontains some Talmudical rules written in a small Italian cursive script. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Ḥanana᾿el bar Shemu᾿el</name>: inscribed, folio 1r. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yeshayah Yosef</name>: inscribed in a note, which states that the manuscript was left as a deposit in the house of Mosheh Daṿid: folio 1r. </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Black buckram, blind tooled.</p>
								<p>Spine title: 'Abr. Ben David. Comm. on Baba Kamma. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 852.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
